///|
pub fn feature_rater_skill_markdown() -> String {
  [
    "---",
    "name: editor-feature-rater",
    "description: Read course material and current UI evidence, rate missing editor-mode features, and select the lowest-scoring/highest-priority next implementation target.",
    "---",
    "",
    "# Editor Feature Rater Skill",
    "",
    "You choose the next editor-mode implementation target from evidence, not from a fixed list.",
    "",
    "## Required Output",
    "",
    "Write `raw/editor-pipeline/next-feature.json` as JSON with this shape:",
    "",
    "```json",
    "{",
    "  \"contract\": \"\{feature_selection_result_contract()}\",",
    "  \"selected_feature\": \"short kebab-case id\",",
    "  \"title\": \"human-readable feature title\",",
    "  \"score\": 1,",
    "  \"why_lowest\": \"why this is the weakest/highest-leverage missing feature\",",
    "  \"excluded_implemented_features\": [\"feature ids excluded because they are already accepted\"],",
    "  \"course_evidence\": [\"course page or exercise path plus short reason\"],",
    "  \"current_gap\": \"what current UI/pipeline lacks\",",
    "  \"implementation_hint\": \"smallest next code slice\",",
    "  \"acceptance\": [\"observable acceptance criterion\"],",
    "  \"rejected_candidates\": [",
    "    {\"feature\":\"candidate id\",\"score\":5,\"reason\":\"why not selected\"}",
    "  ]",
    "}",
    "```",
    "",
    "## Scoring Rubric",
    "",
    "- `1-2`: essential course requirement, visibly missing, and ideal for proving PlanBook-to-code execution.",
    "- `3-4`: important and partly missing, but not the best proof target.",
    "- `5-7`: useful but already partially represented or less central.",
    "- `8-10`: already strong enough or not relevant to editor mode.",
    "",
    "## Quality Rules",
    "",
    "- Use the existing course pages as source of truth.",
    "- Prefer features that make editor mode a real pipeline, not cosmetic UI polish.",
    "- Exclude features already listed in `FEATURE_SELECTION_CONTEXT.md`; repeating an accepted feature is an invalid selection.",
    "- Read `CURRENT_UI_EVIDENCE.md` before opening large UI source files. It is generated from current runtime/code evidence and should be sufficient for normal feature selection.",
    "- Prefer file-only completion: write `next-feature.json` first, then return the same concise JSON.",
    "- Name specific evidence paths.",
    "- Keep the implementation hint bounded enough for one repair packet.",
    "- If evidence is insufficient, still choose the best-supported candidate and state the uncertainty.",
    "",
    @skill_quality.exploration_quality_contract_section(),
  ].join("\n")
}
